
After creating the backend folder, cd backend:
Prerequisites
$npm init -y
$ npm install express --save
$npm install --save-dev @babel/core @babel/node @babel/preset-env


Then create this file inside src folder: ".babelrc"
Inside ".bablerc" file write this and save:
{
    "presets": ["@babel/preset-env"]
}

To run our express application:
$npx babel-node src/server.js 

For being able to use json data in our code:
$npm install --save body-parser